\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Radar comparison across six dimensions. AgenticContract scores highest overall due to its purpose-built design for agent governance, though auditability is limited by single-writer constraints and agent-native integration relies on text-matching rather than a full policy language. OPA and Cedar excel at authorization expressiveness but lack governance depth (risk limits, obligations, violations) and agent-native integration.}}{6}{figure.caption.14}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:radar}{{7}{6}{Radar comparison across six dimensions. AgenticContract scores highest overall due to its purpose-built design for agent governance, though auditability is limited by single-writer constraints and agent-native integration relies on text-matching rather than a full policy language. OPA and Cedar excel at authorization expressiveness but lack governance depth (risk limits, obligations, violations) and agent-native integration}{figure.caption.14}{}}
